text: František Staněk (born 24 April 1944) is a Czech coxswain who represented Czechoslovakia. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome with the men's coxed pair where they were eliminated in the round one repêchage. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:Living people Category:Czechoslovak male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Czechoslovakia Category:Rowers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:People from Jindřichův Hradec Category:Coxswains (rowing)
